NOTE:



I forgot to mention that the CW6 stopped transmitting data for ~2 minutes during the
thermal stimuli today. I left everything running and put a couple back-to-back stim
marks in the data at the time the data acquisition resumed. As such, we'll need to
label the stim marks in that data set in two groups and not use the data near the
transition period ~300 seconds.


No problem. The CW6 stopped transmitting at 312 seconds. The stim marks at 318 and
319 are just to call out the fact that the system stopped and then resumed near
there. They should be removed. Stimuli that are probably still useable: 29:30:269
and 334:30:604. I'll personally delete all of the stim marks and add them back using
those two ranges.

 - Chris
